The paper focuses on multimodal retrieval using deep hashing techniques, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) aspects. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep hashing framework that involves learning semantic labels, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), making cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the bit balance property, which is related to computer architecture (CA) and hardware design (HD), making cs.AR (Computer Architecture) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on three widely-used datasets, which falls under the category of experimental design and analysis (EA), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a likely sub-category as well.
